      <section eId="sec_44_14_81">
        <num>44-14-81</num>
        <content>
          <p>Powers of sale in the conveyances of real property to secure debt shall not be exercised after an action to foreclose the instrument is barred. A sale or conveyance under power in such instrument after an action to foreclose the instrument is barred shall be absolutely void and not merely voidable.</p>
          <p>(Ga. L. 1941, p. 487, ยง 3.)</p>
